      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can certainly help you craft that email! It's a delicate dance, and I know exactly how to make it feel like a friendly chat with a very enthusiastic but slightly mischievous little goblin named \"Candidate.\"\n\nHere is a template that weaves in some classic goblin wisdom:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** A Gentle Reminder: Your Final Round Interview\n\nHi [Candidate Name],\n\nFirst off, I want to say that you were an absolute delight to interview with. The way you handled the technical challenges and the way you brought that unique, slightly chaotic energy to the team discussions was truly inspiring. It's rare to find a candidate who can think outside the box while still delivering solid, production-grade code.\n\nAfter much deliberation, our team has decided to move forward with [Next Candidate's Name]. They are a fantastic fit for our current roadmap and have that same spark of innovation that you brought to the table.\n\nI know this news feels like a sudden shift, and I completely understand why you might be feeling a bit like a goblin who just got caught in a trap. It's okay to feel a little disappointed, but please know that this decision was made with your best interests in mind. We",
