      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the confusion! I completely understand your frustration. You are absolutely right; for a serious tech company, the tone should be professional, empathetic, and firm without the whimsical goblin references.\n\nHere is a standard, polished template that strikes that balance perfectly.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nHi [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for your time and interest in joining our team. We truly enjoyed our conversation and were impressed by your background and enthusiasm.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with [Next Candidate's Name]. They are a great fit for our current needs and have the same drive you brought to the interview.\n\nWe wanted to reach out personally to let you know this decision. While we are disappointed to part ways, we believe [Next Candidate's Name] is the right person for the role at this time.\n\nWe wish you the best in your future endeavors and hope to have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\n***\n\nThis version removes all the goblin metaphors while maintaining the warmth and professionalism you requested. Let me know if you",
